[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering servlet API version**\n\nI'm weighing the options for using servlet-api 2.3 versus 2.4 for JDK 25. While 2.4 is already successfully used in the existing setup, the library’s requirement is 2.3. Since the current scaffold uses 2.4, I might prefer that for consistency and reduced risk, especially with test implementation scope. However, servlet-api 2.3 does include necessary classes and methods like `getHeaders`, but might not have some newer methods. It seems testing with 2.3 may simplify mock setups.\n\n**Reviewing test implementation**\n\nI'm wondering about the existing tests and whether they use Mockito. It seems they don't implement `HttpServletRequest`, which makes me think they might be using mocks through dynamic proxies instead. I need to check the imports in `InputContextImplTest` to clarify this. Getting a clearer picture of how these tests are set up will help me understand the approach used and whether it aligns with the servlet API considerations I've been thinking about.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_07c7fb40beef0585016a42c5710e448197a1b5b9a5317dc513\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQsV4zb_-RVcZOVfbujfctIiuWGIx83853X9AScxgMAvRxp9GSkYuXphODn5P_9rmxN7i-9SY1jKPHt0RRpBM4vmeNL5kT3U8CZ9EGsLFRFQnxptfwwDgYnJBPut1pnLEOFJW_fW0ZNex5awZ_o6wWWuLo8GETOM3NT8a2n9gpiKx5yWHN4UW_FnCSmaHvT8qUnGGSFFa1uGiojOcHDEzNP0Hlv2CsdVg9BOe71xj6XW1h2Hr7l1IG5_73nK3XCbXAS1fMAWLQ-jba5O_DPj6A7OU5yMHDGY51k9ACwUILOqHhhETl9uvPM1T-xzbFcIsv-ayrPLpCBaZ3khrTiSBPuth1ou4APXNrboAMUT604Hz4qSh5zpawYBSme8Wui--CcNpbXEAIo8PMG3avr5skG28GWwL489hZUk9CsOzwuxNF21GWvSsXitKRIS48-NGxQdUka1IgbzS3kS4iUhIX_K0xWOjzEHdNTPx3S01GIZFP5hGYYBpfJ4Z_ZMzfEqwwOyAZXy6duhOIeoM77nJyHRLW-OkI9QtHOY3nP7vhoB4HnhbEJooR5Uj6zZ0GbWa06HO5Ci6vRiy3sRoI4r8p_isjPuGXZXUWNnqJL8Zc19aeduo4chNyxi9BOENotJ6PCQGau86KTcprtxyiMoz5T6MEeXmyR5BO7AwWWPmMZty4TpDQ0dgC8_-mvaauTqAsNa4A5U3xk2fg5